hackathon-description-text: Firebird Hacks I is the first hackathon being organized by Fremont High School's programming club. Firebird Hacks encourages its participants to dive into the field of computer science and express their creativity through computer science. Firebird Hacks provides everyone with equal opportunity to express their creativity by programming.
hackathon-eligibility: Individuals between the age of 13 and 18 years old can participate in Firebird Hacks.

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: - Google Minis for each person on the winning team
- 4 Total Xbox Games and PS4 Games by EA
- Raspberry Pi Zero give to each person
- Amazon $200 Gift Certificate given to each person in the winning team.

hackathon-location-google-maps: https://maps.google.com/?q=6600 Dumbarton Cir, Fremont, CA 94555, USA

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion: How was the overall design of the submitted project.
How ambitious was the team in terms of the degree of technical ability that was required to implement the solution.
